cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM. 

This paper deals with image generation tasks and proposes a new unsupervised algorithm for training GANs that learns disentangled style and content representations of the data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of Adaptive Instance Normalization (AdaIN) layers, which are commonly used in style transfer tasks, indicating a possible connection to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves training GANs, which is a common topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the decomposition of image representations, which could be related to cs.GR (Graphics).
